Unless I see clear evidence that the DVD set for season 2 includes a replacement disk for Season 1's disk 2, which was missing from all the season 1 sets, I will not be getting this.  I bought the DVDs and could only view episodes 1-3 and 7-13 because the disk with episodes 4-6 was missing (actually, it was printed and included but had the wrong episodes on it so you got 2 disks with disk 4 content but no disks with disk 2 content).  This was true of both replacement sets, and I believe that the seller eventually discovered that all his copies were similarly affected, so it seems to have been a widespread problem, so unless the studio makes good in the season 2 set, forget it.
